natural problem: Simplify $(3-2i)^2$. (Your answer should be of the form $a+bi$.)

a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-2))"
shows  "a^2 = Complex (Re 5) (Im (-12))"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify $(3-2i)^2$. (Your answer should be of the form $a+bi$.) The final Answer is 5-12i
 ### Proof
 $(3-2i)^2 = (3-2i)(3-2i)= 3(3) + 3(-2i) -2i(3) - 2i(-2i) = 9-6i-6i -4 = \boxed{5-12i}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes a :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-2))"
shows  "a^2 = Complex (Re 5) (Im (-12))"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
